                                                                            Detecting Web Attacks — Task-Wise Answers
Task 2 — Web Attack Basics

• What kind of web attack involves overwhelming a web server with requests? → DDoS
• Which attack technique tries to inject SQL into queries? → SQL Injection
• What is the name for tricking a site by sending unexpected input? → Input Validation Attack

Task 3 — Analyzing Logs

• What field in the logs shows a suspicious number of failed login attempts? → status (e.g., 401/403)
• Which IP made the most failed requests? → 198.51.100.23
• Which URI saw the most suspicious traffic? → /wp-login.php

Task 4 — SQL Injection Detection

• What suspicious pattern indicates SQL injection attempts? → ' OR '1'='1
• Which parameter was targeted with SQLi patterns? → username

Task 5 — Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)

• What attack vector typically uses <script> tags to inject JS? → XSS
• Which field in logs showed reflected input? → query string

Task 6 — Brute Force Detection

• Which IP was responsible for repeated POST attempts? → 203.0.113.45
• How many repeated login attempts triggered an alert? → 12
• Flag from brute force task: → THM{BRUTE_FORCE_DETECTED}
